<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Document</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <form
      action="/upload" "/* Basically an url to which we send, Without this the file goes to the url, instead we want to send it to backend */"
      method="post" // It can be anything get pull post | Here we use post because we need to post the information to server
      style="
        display: grid;
        gap: 0.5rem;
        grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
        max-width: 500px;
        margin: 0 auto;
      "
      enctype="multipart/form-data" // We are using this to specify the form that we are sending a file
      // Specifies we are sending across a multi part form and that it sends in pieces and the reason it is multi part is because we are sending a file which has multiple parts. Cant send all parts at once coz it will be very large
    >
      <label for="file">File:</label> 
      <input type="file" id="file" name="file" required />
      <label for="password">Password:</label>
      <input type="password" id="password" name="password" />
      <button style="grid-column: span 2" type="submit">Share</button>
    </form>
  </body>
</html>
